# MCP & OAuth Production

## Required Railway env vars

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `API_PUBLIC_URL` | Public API base — OAuth callback host |
| `FRONTEND_URL` | Redirect after OAuth (onboarding) |
| `CORS_ORIGINS` | Comma-separated Vercel origin(s) |
| `SECRETS_ENCRYPTION_KEY` | Fernet key for OAuth tokens at rest |

OAuth callback URL: `{API_PUBLIC_URL}/api/brokers/robinhood/callback`

## Vercel

- `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` = Railway domain (no trailing slash)
- Redeploy after env changes

## Debugging CORS

Browser CORS errors often mean the API returned **500 without CORS headers**, not a missing origin. Check Railway logs first.

```bash
curl -s -X POST "$API_PUBLIC_URL/api/brokers/robinhood/connect" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"return_path":"/onboarding"}'
```

Expect JSON with `authorization_url`, not `Internal Server Error`.

## Token storage

- Per-user tokens in broker account `meta.mcp` — encrypted via `apps/api/app/core/secrets.py`.
- Global OAuth client registration stored in `app_state` under user `_global`.

## Do not

- Commit `SECRETS_ENCRYPTION_KEY` or OAuth tokens.
- Use `localhost` callback URL in production (`API_PUBLIC_URL` must be set).
